  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Tredcroft was born about 1475, in Billingshurst, Sussex, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Frederost Tredcroft. She married William Bowyer of Petworth about 1495. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 3 daughters. She died before 1528, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt. 1475–Bef. 1528":"umbes 1475–enne 1528","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1475–1537":"1475–1537","1465–1528":"1465–1528","1497–Female":"1497–Surnud","1500–1552":"1500–1552","1501–1552":"1501–1552","1502–Female":"1502–Surnud","1504–1555":"1504–1555","1505–Female":"1505–Surnud","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1450":"1450","before 1504":"enne 1504","Bef. 1528":"enne 1528","1502":"1502","1501":"1501","about 1505":"umbes 1505","1555":"1555","1500":"1500","1465":"1465","1552":"1552","1497":"1497","1475":"1475","about 1502":"umbes 1502","Abt. 1475":"umbes 1475","about 1500":"umbes 1500","about 1497":"umbes 1497","about 1495":"umbes 1495","1528":"1528","1505":"1505","1504":"1504","1537":"1537","Petworth, Sussex, England":"Petworth, Sussex, England","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Billingshurst, Sussex, England":"Billingshurst, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt. 1475–Bef. 1528":"noin 1475–ennen vuotta 15